                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2395: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 24, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. For the Under Secretary. Department’s No. 102, October 19, 5 p.m. On October
                    9 and 12 I recommended Jaramillo’s appointment to the Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs who was unable to induce his acceptance. Therefore, I transmitted your
                    timely message to President Santos on October 21 and as a result Jaramillo now
                    agrees to go to Washington. I will telegraph as soon as his departure date is
                    decided.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
